History of Present Illness (HPI): The patient is adjusting to life in New York, finding it exciting yet overwhelming. They are trying to maintain a routine and prioritize self-care through yoga and city exploration.

Progress Evaluation: The patient has shown significant progress in auditions, feeling good about their performances and connecting well with the material.
Therapeutic Interventions: The patient is using relaxation techniques before auditions to help with focus and calmness.
Next Steps: The patient plans to continue practicing their techniques and is considering taking acting classes to further enhance their skills.
